<!-- Why this matters --><div style="margin-top:16px;background:#fbfdff;border:1px solid #dbe6f3;border-left:5px solid #009ef5;border-radius:14px;padding:14px 16px;">
<div style="font-weight:900;color:#1c2430;margin-bottom:6px;">Why this matters</div>
<div style="color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">The EIR defines the required BIM Uses and information outcomes. This BEP section turns those requirements into an executable plan by confirming <strong>what</strong> applies, assigning <strong>who</strong> delivers it, and checking <strong>readiness</strong> to proceed. This reduces ambiguity, improves accountability, and supports reliable delivery and verification.</div>
</div>
